‚úàÔ∏èPika World Update ‚Äì 28 Jan 2022‚úàÔ∏èEquity markets continued to slide further as interest rate hike expectations weighed on risk-on sentiments. There isn‚Äôt much positive news around the market  given that many corporations drove the idea of supply chain constraints affecting their performance.üóΩApple: Shining once moreüçéShares of Apple in after-hours trading rose sharply as it reported a robust set of results for the December quarter  smashing targets. All business segments except for iPad saw growth. The services segment was the star as it is up 23.8% from last year  well ahead of expectation.While the company cited supply chain constraints  it is mainly on old legacy chips. Thus  analysts expect Apple to continue its drive momentum against a more uncertain macro environment.üì±Robinhood Markets: A poor showingüß∏Shares of Robinhood fell sharply after its first-quarter revenue dropped 35%  a stark contrast from its peak performance a year ago. The wider than expected loss also add worry to the company performance. Much of this loss is attributed to share-based compensation.The company struggled to attract more users to its platform after losing around 100 000 customers in the third quarter. Given the die down of the meme vibe and a weaker crypto trading environment  the company continued to be hurt by a general  more fragile trading environment.Pika World will be taking losses on the position and reducing exposure.üíàMastercard and Visaüè∏Both companies reported decent results  but Wall Street seems to ask for more. Mastercard beats estimates by 6%  but this wasn‚Äôt good enough. The 2022 full-year revenue guidance is also on a disappointing note. The market expects a 20% growth compared to its estimated high-teens forecast.On the flip side  Visa first-quarter result beats estimate and showed strong performance in the e-commerce transaction sphere  given a healthier cross border travel activity in a recovering economy.The market continued to be in limbo  and we expect more downside risk as the participants re-adjust their expectations and adapt to a less accommodative environment. It is a painful journey for Pika Nat  too  building on a more defensive mode.It is 28 Jan  Friday  9 am in Singapore and 9 pm in New York.Pika World wishes all friends a safe and re-charging weekend!

DBS to buy Citi's Taiwan consumer banking business with S$956m premium1. DBS DBS: D05 0% is acquiring the consumer banking business of Citigroup in Taiwan  Citi Consumer Taiwan  via a transfer of assets and liabilities.2. The transaction will see DBS paying Citi cash for the net assets of the business plus a premium of S$956 million  said Singapore's largest lender on Friday (Jan 28) morning.3. As at end-September 2021  Citi Consumer Taiwan had an earning asset base of S$20.3 billion and total deposits of S$15.1 billion - of which 70 per cent are sticky low-cost deposits.More here
